OL,7,FShe said when her sister was killed,
OL,8,Fshe did not understand what honour
OL,9,Fkillings were, but now, "having worked
OL,10,Fin the sector for about six years now,
OL,11,FI have realised the importance of
OL,12,Fspeaking (out) to make sure that girls
OL,13,Flike my sister aren't failed again -
OL,14,Fthat this doesn't happen again, and
OL,15,Fthat police, professionals are
OL,16,Flistening to girls like Banaz and
OL,17,Freally taking their fears seriously.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/11
